The kilogram is defined by setting the Planck constant h exactly to 6.62607015×10−34 J⋅s (J = kg⋅m2⋅s−2), given the definitions of the metre and the second.

The amount of substance of exactly 6.02214076×10^23 elementary entities. This number is the fixed numerical value of the Avogadro constant, NA, when expressed in the unit mol−1.
